    {
      "name": "WAIT",
      "description": "Wait time",
      "help": "Wait time (WAIT)\n\nSpecifies the number of seconds that the program waits for the object to be allocated. If the object cannot be allocated in the specified wait time, a message, which can be detected by a Monitor Message (MONMSG) command, is sent to the program. If one or more device descriptions are in the list of objects to be allocated, the system may wait more than the specified amount of time to attempt the allocation.\n\nWhen allocating distributed data management (DDM) files and distributed files, additional time is required for communications and for allocating files on remote systems. A separate wait time is used for each remote system. When allocating objects with a lock-space-scope, the lock space may override the wait time specified.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *CLS",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*CLS",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "numericOnly": true,
        "valueRelation": {
          "relation": "GE",
          "value": "0"
        }
      },
      "positional": 2,
      "placeholder": "*CLS",
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "SCOPE",
      "description": "Lock scope",
      "help": "Lock scope (SCOPE)\n\nSpecify the scope for this lock request.\n\nAll objects types supported by the OBJ parameter support job-scoped locks. All object types supported by the OBJ parameter support lock-space-scoped locks. When allocating DDM objects with a lock-space-scope, the lock on the remote system is scoped to the job.\n\nLocks scoped to a thread can never conflict with a lock scoped to its containing job, but may conflict with a lock scoped to a different job or any other thread (depending on the lock states involved).",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*JOB",
      "attributes": {
        "restricted": true,
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*JOB",
          "value": "*JOB"
        },
        {
          "label": "*THREAD",
          "value": "*THREAD"
        },
        {
          "label": "*LCKSPC",
          "value": "*LCKSPC"
        }
      ],
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "CONFLICT",
      "description": "Lock conflict action",
      "help": "Lock conflict action (CONFLICT)\n\nSpecify the action to be taken if a lock conflict exists. This parameter is only supported for database files and is ignored for all other objects. The supported database *FILE objects are:",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*NORQSRLS",
      "attributes": {
        "restricted": true,
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*NORQSRLS",
          "value": "*NORQSRLS"
        },
        {
          "label": "*RQSRLS",
          "value": "*RQSRLS"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "examples": [
